description.narrative: The objective of the project is to ensure continued effective use of the rehabilitated national and provincial road network in support of the economic development in Cambodia. It will do so by improving the institutional and technical capacity of the Ministry of Public Works and Transport for road maintenance planning, budgeting and operations, and by expanding and strengthening maintenance activities.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Sch.2; Section I.A.2(e) | Description :Provide annual periodic maint. funding of no less than: (i) $300,000(2009); (ii) $2.5m (2010); (iii) $3.75m (2011); (iv) $4m (2012); (v) $4.25m (2013) | Due Date :15-Jan-2010

Finance Agreement :Sch.2; Section I.A.2(g) | Description :Have tech aud of civil works, goods & Serv fin by Proj & on work referredto in subpara(f) of this para undertaken annually by ind auditors acceptable to the Assoc. & furnish aud reports to Assoc. |Frequency :Yearly

title.narrative: Civil works performed by private contractors

comment.narrative: % of the contracts performed by private contractors
25% of the contracts performed by private contractors.

Most of the Regional Offices have been outsourcing the road maintenance activities to private contractors. Performance BasedContracting approach is being increasingly introduced to replace force account.

title.narrative: Roads in good and fair condition as a share of total classified roads

comment.narrative: Significant improvement has been made since 2008.

title.narrative: Travel time is maintained or reduced

comment.narrative: Travel time for 100 km was 2 hours
Travel time for 100 km was slightly increased from 1 hour and 20 minutes to 1 hour and 35 minutes.

title.narrative: RMDS fully operational with proper usage of software and project level analysis

baseline.value: Basic system in place, further development of technical expertise

target.value: RMDS fully operational in the Road Data Collection and Management Unit;3 year and annual work plans updated annually

actual.value: RMDS is operational and continues to perform its task.

comment.narrative: RDCMU is capable of using RMDS to update annual work plan, running economic and sensitive analyzes on candidate roads to berehabilitated or maintained.

title.narrative: Domestic revenue for routine and periodic maintenance and spot rehabilitation

comment.narrative: National budget for all types of maintenance for 2014 is kept at US$50 million.

title.narrative: MPWT prepares annual maintenance works plan using RMDS and submits budget requests to MEF by June based on medium term program

baseline.value: Delay in the preparation of the budget

target.value: Annual work program and budget prepared and submitted to MEF through ICRRM by June

actual.value: 2015 Annual work program and budget is being prepared and will be submitted to MEF by June 2014.

comment.narrative: The three year road maintenance program (2014 - 2016) was produced and it has been annually updated. As required for 2015 updating,the RDCMU is carrying out the road condition survey till May 2014 and the updating will complete in June 2014.(The first annualmaintenance plan was produced in 2013).

title.narrative: Capacity building of GDPW staff improved in: (a) Design of surface treatments; (b) cost estimates; (c) M&E of road maintenance works; (d) supervision and maintenance works

baseline.value: Lack of capacity within the GDPWT

target.value: 90% of relevant GDPWT staff subject to capacity development program are technically capable in all designated areas

comment.narrative: Out of 149 staff who trained on (i) design of surface treatments, (ii) cost estimates; (iii) M & E of road maintenance works, (iv)supervision and maintenance works, whose knowledge was briefly assessed by RAMO (fair=5%; good=25%, very good=70%).
